{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02502/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02502"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:25:02"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man tailors a dress on a woman."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02502","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02502"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1/7b0384b0-e9c9-4d55-91ad-a76ef15b2897","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:58:56.272Z","creator":"grace","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This scene, along with Reynolds’s aesthetics in general, plays on the Pygmalion myth, most famously told in Ovid’s <em>Metamorphoses</em>, which traces how the titular sculptor falls in love with one of his statues who is granted life by Aphrodite. Reynolds sees his art as giving life to form, to inorganic matter (cloth) in the shape of dresses. Here, he resembles a sculptor carving or giving shape to his love, Alma. The film’s <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW4049377 BCX4\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-20355.html\"><u>closing shot</u></a> emphasizes Alma’s connection to the statue in Reynold’s fitting room.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:957.4158815612392,138.8156123822346,514.2395693135935,469.01749663526255"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1/fa4929c0-ec77-4db2-8fd3-27560fce09f6","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:59:16.822Z","creator":"grace","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>While Alma's dress in this scene is a crude muslin mockup of the dress Reynolds plans to make her, its whiteness foreshadows their future marriage. While this dress is made from the cheapest, most disposable fabric, her clothing gets more luxurious as she becomes further enveloped in Reynolds’s life.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02502/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:435.42395693136024,367.51009421265184,441.8842530282639,657.6581426648722"}}}]}]}]}